snippet.textDisplay: The fun thing about living in the south! In the fall, winter or spring time the temperature and weather conditions can get whack. One day you wake up and your freezing your tits off, you get out of school or off work mid day and then you’re sweating your balls off and then it’s a little comfortable until it freezes again in the middle of the night. The summers are just all out hot and humid and get up to over 100 degrees but because of the humidity, it can feel like 120 degrees outside no joke. Same with rain, sunshine or snow/ sleet. It rains down hard for 10 minutes and is sunny right after the fact or it’s 50 degrees one day and your scraping ice off your windshield in the snow the next. I’m enjoying the series though, lol! I live in Arkansas but you traveled just a couple hours away from where I live in Missouri 😁

Heat rises guys, heaters on the floor (PUT A FIRE DETECTOR IN THERE. THEY ARE LIKEA COUPLE BUCKS!!! Just put a battery in and tape it on the floor or ceiling if ya fancy)
I do road trips up and down the coast and CC all the time for ten years... read this.

Haha the first time you drive super far Inthe USA and rent a shower at a truck stop is always interesting hahaha. Make sure you wear shoes in the shower.
Next.... You guys are literal millionaires. Why didn’t you load more portable heaters in there? Like Bluetooth ones you could hook all up to the same surge protector and then you should have brought a spare car battery and used THAT to charge shit (there’s super simple adapters)... oh wait you guys are rich af..... just get one of those portable battery things you can keep in your trunk and (meant to use to charge you car if it breaks down) then hook ONE surge protector to that and plug all the heaters into it (like 4 lol not 15 or you’ll make a fire) so you can flip them on all at once or charge them all at once if they’re portable. Just put them low, not high, as heat rises and if you put it above you, you’ll never feel it. Put them under the bed but make sure it’s not by anything that can start a fire bc that’s such a small space the smoke will make you pass out before you ever realize it. PUT A FIRE DETECTOR IN THERE. THEY ARE LIKEA COUPLE BUCKS!!!

Lol also.... that’s not just a law in Kansas. It’s a law everywhere... like... for driving.... you pass on the right and cruise in the left if there’s only two lanes. If there’s three then the left is long distance, the right is the slow or “hop on hop off” lane, and the middle is the “passing” lane. Didn’t you take drivers ed lol?Anyway, they usually don’t enforce it and it’s more of an etiquette thing than a law. Though actually tb fair, I’m in NY so maybe that isn’t a law in Cali... but it is in the east coast. That’s the thing but obviously they were using any excuse to look for drugs since you were in a van. When he saw 3 kids in their 20s he was probably PSYCHED like “they gotta at least have weed.” Lol NOPE! Not even a closed bottle of booze. Score one for the good guys lol.
